      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s not intended that the return value be checked here. The time to check return values is when the variable the field is extracted _to_ is used _before_ the implementation returns to the caller. For example, how `pdr-\u003eeffecter_count` is tested above on lines 3444-3447, as it is used below on line 3453. If it\u0027s not used then no explicit test is necessary: the failure tests are batched up by calls to the `pldm_msgbuf_complete*()` APIs. This improves ergonomics in the implementation as this way we don\u0027t require tests after every extraction (or insertion).",
